What still needs attention in the new text

A. One genuine tension to reconcile (worth fixing).
Fourth paragraph:

▎ "...developed as a bounded sensitivity check — deliberately kept as a comparison rather than the primary model ... It ... ultimately became the basis for the final recommendation."

This collides with §7 (line ~2134): "We therefore recommend adopting the capacity-constrained network as the primary implementation plan." A reader sees the capped model demoted to "comparison / sensitivity check" here, but elevated to "primary implementation plan" in the recommendation.

It is reconcilable — "primary model" here means the primary optimization/analytical model (uncapped, fully data-grounded), while the capped model is the recommendation. But the words "primary model" vs. "primary implementation plan" are close enough to jar.
- Fix: disambiguate to "…rather than the primary optimization model…". One word removes the apparent contradiction.

B. Tiny wording nit.

▎ "rendered the model infeasible for a single region"

Imprecise — the whole model is infeasible because of one region, not "for" it.
- Fix: "…infeasible due to a single region."

That's all on the new paragraph. Everything else in it is fine.

